\begin_layout Standard
We assume that firms act separately and independently, and do not attempt
 to unite (form a cartel).
 In such case we can safely assume that all decision-making is identical.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A firm continues to hire more employees, as long as their marginal productivity
 is above their wage - up to the point where the marginal productivity falls
 below the wage.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Firms care about real wage, not about the nominal - i.e not about 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

